            <title><![CDATA[Sony’s DualSense controllers are almost 30 percent off]]></title>
            <link>https://www.theverge.com/gadgets/938029/sony-dualsense-wireless-edge-controller-ps5-pc-deal-sale</link>
            <guid>1531243</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div id="zephr-anchor"><p>Sony has a tradition of marking down its PlayStation 5 hardware a couple of times a year, and one of those opportunities to save is here through June 10th. Its <strong>latest Days of Play sale</strong> is happening at multiple retailers, including <a href="https://www.amazon.com/stores/page/preview?isSlp=1&amp;isPreview=1&amp;asins=B0GJFVK6QV%2CB0FY6PBWWJ%2CB0FY6X2XXY%2CB0FY6Y9WZT%2CB0CJSY6961%2CB0CJTCQRNL%2CB0DHY8DC6R%2CB0FY6VF3Q5%2CB0CQKL4YTB%2CB0DHY92HBL%2CB0FY6X8VFS%2CB0GL96NJL5%2CB0CQKLDWY8%2CB0GFQ2Z3BM%2CB0GFQ2YZM7%2CB0GFQBQ4KZ%2CB0BSYFB99D%2CB0DSQQ1P8D%2CB0CCGYBSW8%2CB0DSQWH9BR%2CB0G5SCBH91%2CB0CMDFSB89%2CB0DSQSX7FB%2CB0GKHMCC5V%2CB0F6F41T4H%2CB0B61YDF5V%2CB098G34GBT%2CB09SW6GCGL%2CB0D5SM3K4Q%2CB0CP4DCK45%2CB0C7WQRCPB%2CB0CJGPSXG4%2CB0B3QWRQL8%2CB08FC5TTBF%2CB0F19GPDW3%2CB0CPYSPHR1%2CB095T8C99C%2CB08QFPS48J%2CB0DX42RXMS%2CB0CTVK7GBM%2CB08QFWWJ8K%2CB09Z7JZW4P%2CB09RDRYF8L%2CB0C1QJ6VHY&amp;pf_rd_t=Events&amp;pf_rd_i=deals&amp;pf_rd_p=b1ab93f1-0f27-4035-81c4-56aebad2af1c&amp;pf_rd_s=slot-14&amp;tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored">Amazon</a>, <a href="https://bestbuy.7tiv.net/c/482924/614286/10014?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fsite%2Fpromo%2Fsave-on-select-playstation" rel="sponsored">Best Buy</a>, <a href="https://click.linksynergy.com/deeplink?id=nOD/rLJHOac&amp;mid=24348&amp;murl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamestop.com%2Flinks%2Fdays-of-play%2Fnew" rel="sponsored">GameStop</a>, <a href="https://goto.walmart.com/c/482924/565706/9383?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fbrand%2Fplaystation%2F10033766" rel="sponsored">Walmart</a>, and at <a href="https://sonyps.prf.hn/click/camref:1101l5nbBL/%5Bp_id:1011l394533%5D/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fdirect.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fdeals%2Fdays-of-play" rel="sponsored">Sony’s site</a> as well. It loops in almost everything that Sony’s PlayStation division has released — games, headphones, DualSense controllers, PSVR 2 headsets — everything except the consoles themselves.</p><p>This post is focusing on <strong>DualSense controllers</strong>, which have dropped to familiar (but welcome) prices. You can get the standard model for $54.99 (originally $74.99) in several single-tone colors. This price is available through <a href="https://sonyps.prf.hn/click/camref:1101l5nbBL/%5Bp_id:1011l394533%5D/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fdirect.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fbuy-accessories%2Fdualsense-wireless-controller-midnight-black-usb-cable-for-pc" rel="sponsored">Sony</a>, <a href="https://bestbuy.7tiv.net/c/482924/614286/10014?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fproduct%2Fsony-interactive-entertainment-dualsense-wireless-controller-for-ps5-pc-mac-mobile-galactic-purple%2FJXHQ37TSPZ" rel="sponsored">Best Buy</a>, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/PlayStation-DualSenseTM-Wireless-Controller-Gaming-Console/dp/B0FY6PBWWJ?th=1&amp;psc=1&amp;tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored">Amazon</a>, <a href="https://goto.walmart.com/c/482924/565706/9383?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FSony-PS5-DualSense-Wireless-Controller-White%2F18248050357%3Fathcpid%3D18248050357%26athpgid%3DAthenaBrandPage%26athcgid%3Dnull%26athznid%3DItemCarousel_ecb4221e-db82-3bd1-9e2a-f366c6970a5f_items%26athieid%3Dv0%26athstid%3DCS020%26athguid%3D-dpA8xAmbbrTxq0Umas1PvlpmMzvdm4OuU8S%26athancid%3Dnull%26athena%3Dtrue%26athbdg%3DL1600" rel="sponsored">Walmart</a>, <a href="https://click.linksynergy.com/deeplink?id=nOD/rLJHOac&amp;mid=24348&amp;murl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamestop.com%2Fgaming-accessories%2Fcontrollers%2Fplaystation-5%2Fproducts%2Fsony-dualsense-wireless-controller-for-playstation-5---white%2F222310.html" rel="sponsored">GameStop</a>, and <a href="https://goto.target.com/c/482924/81938/2092?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.target.com%2Fp%2Fdualsense-wireless-controller-for-playstation-5%2F-%2FA-83377785" rel="sponsored">Target</a>. Some models cost more, including themed controllers based on a game, but are still each $20 off their normal prices.</p><p>The standard model is fantastic for PC players, not just for those who own a PlayStation 5. Its immersive haptics and resistance triggers feel great to use with games that support the features. Otherwise, it’s a very comfortable gamepad to use on any platform that supports Bluetooth.</p><p>As you may already know, Sony also makes the <strong>DualSense Edge</strong>, a high-end alternative that has replaceable thumbstick modules, customizable back paddles, and a function key that grants you the ability to swap control schemes on-the-fly. The $199 model is now down to $169 in white or black, the same price that Sony offers for <a href="https://sonyps.prf.hn/click/camref:1101l5nbBL/%5Bp_id:1011l394533%5D/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fdirect.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fcertified-refurbished" rel="sponsored">refurbished units</a>. You can find this deal at <a href="https://sonyps.prf.hn/click/camref:1101l5nbBL/%5Bp_id:1011l394533%5D/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fdirect.playstation.com%2Fen-us%2Fbuy-accessories%2Fdualsense-edge-wireless-controller-midnight-black" rel="sponsored">PlayStation’s site</a>, as well as at <a href="https://www.amazon.com/PlayStation-DualSense-Edge-Wireless-Controller-5/dp/B0BSYFB99D?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored">Amazon</a>, <a href="https://bestbuy.7tiv.net/c/482924/614286/10014?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fproduct%2Fsony-interactive-entertainment-dualsense-edge-wireless-controller-for-ps5-pc-mac-mobile-midnight-black%2FJXHQ3CXX9X" rel="sponsored">Best Buy</a>, <a href="https://goto.walmart.com/c/482924/565706/9383?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FSony-PS5-DualSense-Edge-Wireless-Controller-Midnight-Black%2F14938419884%3Fathcpid%3D14938419884%26athpgid%3DAthenaBrandPage%26athcgid%3Dnull%26athznid%3DProductTileCollection_82857b3e-e0ad-37e7-aff3-82f23fe87b6f_items%26athieid%3Dv0%26athstid%3DCS020%26athguid%3DBAgTQAK4-Ug912fwD9lJGs_NkbPVekrhC8W5%26athancid%3Dnull%26athena%3Dtrue%26athbdg%3DL1600%26selectedSellerId%3D0" rel="sponsored">Walmart</a>, <a href="https://click.linksynergy.com/deeplink?id=nOD/rLJHOac&amp;mid=24348&amp;murl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamestop.com%2Fgaming-accessories%2Fcontrollers%2Fplaystation-5%2Fproducts%2Fsony-dualsense-edge-wireless-controller-for-playstation-5%2F359710.html" rel="sponsored">GameStop</a>, and <a href="https://goto.target.com/c/482924/81938/2092?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.target.com%2Fp%2Fdualsense-edge-wireless-controller-for-playstation-5%2F-%2FA-94894749" rel="sponsored">Target</a>.</p><div data-product-filter="" id="product-card-dmcyOnByb2R1Y3Q6MjI2MDA="><p><span>$<!-- -->169</span></p><div><p>Sony’s pro-style controller, the DualSense Edge, might suffer from shorter battery life than the standard DualSense model, but it features great software integration with the PlayStation 5 and plenty of customizable components.</p></div></div><div><form><div><h2>Verge Shopping</h2><p><span>Sign up to get the best deals on products we’ve found and tested sent to your inbox.</span></p></div></form></div><div><p><span><strong>Follow topics and authors</strong> from this story to see more like this in your personalized homepage feed and to receive email updates.</span></p><ul><li id="follow-author-article_footer-dmcyOmF1dGhvclByb2ZpbGU6MTU2Ng=="><span aria-expanded="false" aria-haspopup="true" role="button" tabindex="0"><span><span><svg width="9" height="9" viewBox="0 0 9 9" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-label="Follow"><path d="M5 0H4V4H0V5H4V9H5V5H9V4H5V0Z"></path></svg></span><span>Cameron Faulkner</span></span></span></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li></ul></div></div></div><br/><br/>https://www.theverge.com/gadgets/938029/sony-dualsense-wireless-edge-controller-ps5-pc-deal-sale]]></content:encoded>
